        <p class="bento-desc">Originality.ai launched in 2022 and has consistently outperformed GPTZero and Copyleaks on unedited AI text — 97%+ claimed accuracy, 85–97% in our testing. The all-in-one suite (AI detection, plagiarism, fact-checking, readability, team management) is well-built. But accuracy tanks on human-edited AI drafts, false positives are a genuine problem for technical writers and non-native English speakers, and the tool has no SEO capabilities whatsoever.</p>
        <ul class="bento-list">
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Best for: content agencies, publishers, educators verifying AI use</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Price: from $14.95/mo (Pro, 2,000 credits)</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Strength: accuracy on unedited AI text, full-site scanning, team management</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Weakness: false positives, drops to 60–75% accuracy on edited AI, zero SEO</li>
