        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">Two important caveats to understand before buying: accuracy drops significantly on content that's been human-edited after AI generation (60–75% detection rate on the most common business workflow), and false positives are a real problem — technical writing, formal prose, and non-native English speakers get flagged frequently. Stanford research found false positive rates exceeding 50% across detectors on some text types. Use with judgment, not as a binary pass/fail gate.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROS / CONS -->
