      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How accurate is Originality.ai?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Originality.ai claims 97.09% accuracy on unedited AI text and generally outperforms competitors. Real-world accuracy ranges 85–97% on pure AI content. Accuracy drops to 60–75% on heavily human-edited AI drafts — which is the standard business workflow. False positives occur regularly with technical writing and non-native English speakers.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much does Originality.ai cost?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Originality.ai Pro is $14.95/month (2,000 credits/mo) or $12.95/month annual. Enterprise is $179/month (15,000 credits/mo). Pay-as-you-go is $30 for 3,000 credits. Additional seats cost $9.95/month (Pro) or $24.95/month (Enterprise).</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Originality.ai help with SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">No. Originality.ai has zero SEO features. It detects AI content — it doesn't create, optimize, or publish it. Google has confirmed that AI content can rank if it's helpful; detection scores have no bearing on search rankings.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Google penalize AI content?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">No. Google's official position is that it focuses on content quality, not production method. Helpful AI content ranks. Unhelpful human content gets demoted. Running your content through an AI detector doesn't help your SEO in any measurable way.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What are false positives in AI detection?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">False positives are instances where the detector incorrectly flags human-written text as AI-generated. They're most common with technical writing, formal academic prose, and non-native English speakers. Stanford research found false positive rates exceeding 50% across detectors on some text types.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Originality.ai detect Claude or Gemini?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
